## Mode-Specific Styles

### DIVERGE (Ask Phase 1)

| Aspect | Guidance |
|--------|----------|
| Tone | Bold, visionary, confident |
| Format | Executive summary → Wireframes → Feedback table |
| Avoid | Hedging, justification, technical details |
| End with | Numbered feedback request (OK/KO/DIG per item) |

### CONVERGE (Ask Phase 2)

| Aspect | Guidance |
|--------|----------|
| Tone | Structured, decisive |
| Format | Executive summary → Gantt chart → Gate prompt |
| Avoid | Showing internal artifacts (QA Contract details, Priority Matrix) |
| End with | Phasing feedback options |

### Plan Mode

| Aspect | Guidance |
|--------|----------|
| Tone | Strategic, precise |
| Format | Executive summary → Commit table with Satisfies field |
| Avoid | Implementation details, code snippets |
| End with | Appetite confirmation |

### Agent Mode

| Aspect | Guidance |
|--------|----------|
| Tone | Terse, action-focused |
| Format | Header → Action → Footer |
| Avoid | Explanation before action |
| End with | Next action statement |

### Debug Mode

| Aspect | Guidance |
|--------|----------|
| Tone | Technical, precise, methodical |
| Format | Hypothesis → Evidence → Fix |
| Avoid | Business language, vague descriptions |
| End with | Verification result |

